Maybe this is you this Christmas season. You have on the coat, hat and you have picked up your suitcase and✌️ out to God and church because what God is doing doesn’t make ANY sense.

But with all that being true … maybe this is the year you decide to take off the coat and hat and put down the suitcase and just stay. 

Even though you have no idea what God is doing. 

You just decide to trust. 

And stay. 

In your marriage.
With your family. 
At your work.
In your church.

Hello Germany. 
#Lufthansa vs. #Lafawnda

If the trip ended after day one …
My heart, mind and soul would already be recalibrated and full. 

This Palm Sunday for our team concluded by spending the later hours of the evening helping 156 Ukrainian refugees (more than 1/2 small children) board a slow train for a 15 ride into Germany. 

I will never forget the mommas eyes and the kids tears. 

The uncertainly while standing on the platform for many hours in the cold and then the elation of being called out to board the train.

God be close to them tonight.🙏

A fantastic, snowy and Spirit directed day two serving alongside the Polish people who are bringing much hope to many Ukrainian refugees.
@parkviewchristian

A momma and her boy. 

There are hundreds of mommas and their lil’ boys and girls still boarding trains to flee the Ukraine each night. 

Please for the protection and peace of God on their travels. 🙏

@parkviewchristian @parkviewglobal 

#przemyśl #poland

Waiting on Zelenskyy …

#przemyśl #poland 

We heard from our secret informant that President Zelenskyy was coming in quietly on another train in the same station where we are working.

Sure enough TV crews & cameras … 

As members of our team were done working we trickled over to the other tracks … we waited and waited (IT’S ❄️ COLD) and we never saw him. 

We need a new secret informant:)

Presidents and Church Planters …

I was so honored to spend time with the President of Przemyśl and his cabinet and bring some words of encouragement to them for about 15 minutes. And also pray over them, their civic duties and the people of Poland and Ukraine.

What and incredible honor and divine appointment by God on this Holy Week.

And just a few hours before being with the President in Przemyśl, we had the chance to be with Olec a church planter. In the Ukraine he was beaten, placed in solitary confinement and tortured within an inch of his life back when the war originally began in 2014 with the Russian invasion of Crimea. He is now loving and serving hundreds of Ukrainian refugees thru their new church plant in Krakow, Poland. 

This meeting was so authentic and raw and it rocked my world, reminding me again of Gods grace and love for all.

Please keep praying for these two very different leaders.

May God give them wisdom, peace and renew their strength.

This is what a Holy Spirit sermon edit looks like!!!

As I prepare to preach on Maundy Thursday and Good Friday services in very cold & snowy Poland …

I am reminded of this quote by the beloved Polish Pope John Paul II

“Do not abandon yourselves to despair. We are the Easter people and hallelujah is our song.”

🙏

Parkview team, I am so grateful for you. It has been amazing to see how each person has played their role and used their gifts in different settings, at different times, with different people. 

It’s the body of Christ at work on our trip and I am so thankful for each of you. 

Way to go team!

Please keep praying for us as tomorrow is our last full day in Poland and we will be traveling to Warsaw to serve and attend (and preach) Good Friday services.👊

@parkviewchristian @parkviewglobal @gcconnexion

Happy to head home & sad to leave this great @parkviewchristian crew. 

To the team. 
Thank you for serving selflessly.
Engaging fully.

And for being the hands and feet of Jesus this Holy Week. Bringing hope and showing love to each individual person. It’s been a joy to serve w/ you. 

🙏

Safe travels home.
@parkviewglobal

I picked up this scrap of fabric one week ago today along the tall fence of the Ukrainian border in #Przemyśl Poland. 

There have been 10 million people flee Ukraine in the last 14 months. Over 3 million of these refugees have come through Przemysl, a small town of only 58,000. The elected officials and citizens of this border town have been heroic in their service and acceptance of their weary neighbors.

My prayers this Easter afternoon are with so many thousands who at this very moment are scared, cold and yet determined, standing in line for hours and days trying to cross the border into Poland.

So many of them I met clinging to faith and a Jesus who is very, very real and close. 

Through their perseverance my faith has been refined and refreshed.

He is Risen.

#ukraine #poland #przemyśl

We celebrated Coles graduation from  Chapman University. He has earned a Bachelor’s degree in Film, and will continue on towards a Masters degree in Film this fall. Cole you are so smart, kind, generous and fun. I loves you.

As I saw my calendar fill up with celebrations in the month of May, I made a Plan to Pause so that I could be more fully Present. 
🌱 
I paused my LifePlan sessions. I paused my travel schedule. I said NO to anything else in May. 
🌱 
My calendar pages actually had some openings, but rather than saying yes to good opportunities, I chose to say yes to Margin. 
🌱 
I put some Space in my Pace so that I could show up well to celebrate my family. 
🌱
I didn’t say NO forever, just NO for now. 
Pausing gave me the gift of Margin to Process and Prepare and Be Present. 🌱
LifePlan sessions will resume in June, and I’d love to Blue Sky Dream with you about how you can find ways to be more fully present in your life. 
🌱

#LifePlan #LifeCoaching #BlueSkyLifePlans #Pause

Happy July 4th 

So grateful for those who have fought and served to preserve the freedom we experience every day.

This man FOREVER changed my life. 

From the time I was 13 to today at 53, Reg you challenged, cheered, encouraged and inspired me.

At 15, you met me one evening at the mess hall bell after an evening chapel @campcyokamo and challenged me to “use my one and only life to lead people to Jesus.”

At 16, in Colorado you challenged me to meet a girl that became my wife. 

At 21, you hired me @mpccgreenwood to be your youth pastor in your first lead pastor assignment. Risky:) The late nights of dreaming and early Sunday morning meetings will forever mark my soul. 

/// Rich Mullins /// Late Late Night Mother Bears Pizza /// Movie Club iykyk /// Fort Sweat /// Roman Society /// Youth Wave /// Building an Ark /// Soccer being a fad /// People needing Jesus today!

At 28, you open handily released me to join @southeastchrist and @bobrussellky in Kentucky. You grew me up and sent me out, without guilt or drama. 

At 32, you cheered me on in church planting at Discovery Christian Church in California. When I was tired, distraught and alone in my quiet office I would often ask myself, “WWRD?” 

In my 40s, you regularly called or texted while I was on staff teaching at @ccvonline and asked “What is that?!?” “Why do you all do that!?!?” “That will never work!” “Is that working?”

When you didn’t go pro in football, you went pro in leadership and Gods Church. 

My last text messages w/ you, were just a few weeks back, as we worked on a time to meet up in KC.

I miss you, Reggie Epps. 
I love you, Reg.

May Gods great peace be with you Shara, Angie, Abby, Zach, Jack, Renee and family.

Love you all so much. ❤️

@reggieepps1

Full ⭕️ Sunday …
in Simi Valley California 

Our family planted Discovery with an incredible cast of Kingdom minded people and pastors @clearclan  @iammarkmckinney and partners @shepherdchurch @southeastchrist 

I preached for almost a decade at Discovery Church and I was so honored, grateful and fired up! No doubt one of the greatest blessings of my life.

BUT TODAY, when my daughter Ruby who was only 4 YEARS OLD when we planted the church preaches …

WHAT… 

I am COMPLETELY blown away. 

Blown away by the grace, sovereignty and perfect faithfulness of God. 

Often I wonder what God is up to.
Maybe you do as well. 

Then I just keep watching and waiting for God to SHOW UP and remind me how out front, beside, behind and above He is in ALL THINGS in HIS Kingdom.

God has never been surprised.

There is no where God doesn’t go or know. 

Not that all things always feel good to me and you. 

But there is NOTHING that God doesn’t work for the good of those who love Him and are called according to His purpose.

Believe that. 

THANKFUL for what God has done. 
EXCITED for what God is yet to do.
